      "text": "Elfriede is a village concealed deep within the forest's embrace.\n\nIt had been so long since I last roamed these lands that I failed to realize the territory was under nightly assault by bat swarms, leaving the villagers stricken with fear.\n\nClearly, these creatures were blood servants kept by the Vassals out in the wild. Since the arrival of winter forced most beasts into hibernation, the ravenous servants redirected their hunger toward this defenseless village.\n\nThough time was pressing on the survey, saving lives took precedence. I used what remained of my medical knowledge to tend to the wounded. Once their conditions stabilized, I made my way back. Along the way, I recalled each wandering blood servant, escorting them back to the castle to return to the Vassal, accompanied by a cartload of Pure Blood Essence to soothe their terrible thirst.\n\nOnce the crisis passed, I let out a deep sigh of relief. However, an entire day had elapsed, causing the time-sensitive survey task to be marked as failed.\n\nJust as I lifted my pen to write Agnes a letter explaining the circumstances, a sudden wave of bewilderment stirred within my heart. As those blood servants fluttered toward me, I distinctly heard a girl's piercing scream—a voice that carried something deeply unsettling.",
